    "On the orthogonal complement of H C both t S (a)t S ′ (b) and t S ′ (b)t S (a) vanish because at least one string-net constraint on one of the collar regions C S or C S ′ is violated.",
    "9.49Let C ′ ⊂ C be finite regions such that Σ C \\ Σ C ′ is an annulus.",
    "Then there are unique boundary components S ∈ Bd(Σ C) \\ Bd(Σ C ′), andS ′ ∈ Bd(Σ C ′) \\ Bd(Σ C).",
    "Suppose ρ ∈ D C satisfies boundary conditions of type X ∈ Irr Z(C) at boundary component S. Let ρ ′ = Tr C 0 \\C ′ 0 {ρ}be the restriction of ρ to the region C ′.",
    "Then ρ ′ ∈ D C ′ satisfies maximally mixed boundary conditions of type X at boundary component S ′."
